import Oseledets.Krieger.ZIterate
import Mathlib.MeasureTheory.MeasurableSpace.EventuallyMeasurable
import Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.QuasiMeasurePreserving

/-!
# The coding layer for Krieger's finite generator theorem: two-sided recovery (Krieger M3)

This file is the **ŌÉ-algebra recovery core** of Krieger's finite generator theorem. The classical
proof (Krieger 1970; Einsiedler‚ÄďLindenstrauss‚ÄďWard *Entropy in Ergodic Theory* ¬ß3) builds a finite
`Fin k`-valued partition `P` by *coding* the columns of a Rokhlin tower so that the two-sided
`P`-itinerary of a.e. point recovers its full itinerary under a fixed countable generator `Q`. The
combinatorial heart ‚ÄĒ that `log k > h` forces the number of `N`-names to be `‚Č§ kŠīļ` up to `őĶ`, so a
`Fin k` code exists ‚ÄĒ is supplied upstream (the name-count layer M2, the Rokhlin tower M1). What
remains, and is proved here unconditionally, is the **recovery half**: *once* a candidate code `P`
has the property that every cell of `Q` is recovered, **mod 0**, by the two-sided `P`-saturation,
`P` two-sidedly generates **mod 0** whenever `Q` does.

## Why *mod 0*: generators in ergodic theory generate up to null sets

The classical Krieger construction produces a code map that is defined and invertible only
**őľ-almost everywhere**, so it recovers each generator cell only **modulo a őľ-null set**. This is
not an artefact of the formalization: in ergodic theory a "generator" *always* means **mod 0** ‚ÄĒ a
partition generates the ŌÉ-algebra *up to null sets* ‚ÄĒ because the ambient ŌÉ-algebra `mőĪ` of a
standard-Borel space is **not** `őľ`-complete, so an a.e.-defined code can never establish a
*literal* ŌÉ-algebra equality with `mőĪ`. (See Glasner, *Ergodic Theory via Joinings*; Einsiedler‚Äď
Lindenstrauss‚ÄďWard, *Entropy in Ergodic Theory*, Ch. 2 on generators; Downarowicz ¬ß4.2, where the
strong-generator condition is `ūĚďĎ = ŌÉ(‚čÉ‚āô T‚ĀŅ őĪ)` **mod őľ**.) The literal equality
`twoSidedSat e P = mőĪ` is therefore *too strong / non-standard*, and the unconditional Krieger
construction provably cannot discharge it; the mod-0 condition is the faithful one.

We formalize "mod 0" with Mathlib's **`MeasureTheory.eventuallyMeasurableSpace m‚āÄ (ae őľ)`**: the
ŌÉ-algebra of sets that are `=ŠĶź[őľ]`-equal to an `m‚āÄ`-measurable set (the `őľ`-completion of the
sub-ŌÉ-algebra `m‚āÄ`). Crucially this keeps every statement at the level of an order relation `‚Č§`
between `MeasurableSpace őĪ` *values*, with the ambient measure `őľ` fixed against `mőĪ` ‚ÄĒ so the
proofs never rewrite the ŌÉ-algebra index of `őľ` (which would break, since `Measure őĪ` is indexed by
its `MeasurableSpace`).

## The two-sided saturation and its (literal and mod-0) shift-invariance

For `e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ` and a finite partition `P`, write
`twoSidedSat e P := ‚®Ü n : ‚Ą§, comap (e‚ĀŅ) ŌÉ(P)`
for the ŌÉ-algebra generated by the whole two-sided `P`-itinerary. The single structural fact that
drives everything is **shift-invariance**: pulling `twoSidedSat e P` back by any iterate `eŠĶź` lands
inside `twoSidedSat e P` again, because reindexing the `‚Ą§`-supremum `n ‚Ü¶ n + m` is a bijection of
`‚Ą§` (`comap_twoSidedSat_le`). This is precisely where two-sidedness (`‚®Ü` over `‚Ą§`, not `‚Ąē`) is
load-bearing: a forward `‚Ąē`-supremum is *not* shift-invariant under the backward iterate `e‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.

The mod-0 layer lifts this: for a **measure-preserving** `e`, preimage under `eŠĶź` commutes with the
`őľ`-completion (`comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_le`, using that a measure-preserving map is
quasi-measure-preserving so `s =ŠĶź t ‚üĻ f‚ĀĽ¬Ļs =ŠĶź f‚ĀĽ¬Ļt`), and the completion is monotone and idempotent
(`eventuallyMeasurableSpace_mono`, `eventuallyMeasurableSpace_idem`). These give mod-0
shift-invariance (`comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_twoSidedSat_le`) and the mod-0 recovery
monotonicity (`twoSidedSat_mono_of_codes`), so a mod-0 generator `Q` lifts to a mod-0 generator `P`
(`IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0.of_codes`).

## The recovery machinery consumed by the coding layer

The headline's coding step is phrased through the **cross-layer** predicate
`Oseledets.Krieger.CodesTwoSidedMod0c` (`Generator.lean`), which packages the **mod-0** recovery
hypothesis `ŌÉ(Q) ‚Č§ eventuallyMeasurableSpace (twoSidedSat e P) (ae őľ)` ‚ÄĒ every cell of `Q` is
recovered mod 0 by the two-sided `P`-saturation ‚ÄĒ and turns the *existence* of a `Fin k`-valued
`P` with that property into `IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0 e P`. This file supplies the `Fintype`-layer
machinery that predicate is built on: the two-sided saturation `twoSidedSat`, its (literal and
mod-0) shift-invariance, the őľ-completion functoriality, and the recovery-monotonicity lemmas
(`twoSidedSat_mono_of_codes`, `IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0.of_codes`) promoting a mod-0 generator `Q`
to a mod-0 generator `P` once every cell of `Q` is recovered mod 0 by the two-sided `P`-itinerary.

## Main definitions

* `Oseledets.Krieger.twoSidedSat`: the two-sided itinerary ŌÉ-algebra `‚®Ü n : ‚Ą§, comap (e‚ĀŅ) ŌÉ(P)`.
* `Oseledets.Krieger.IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0`: `P` two-sidedly generates **mod 0**.

## Main results

* `Oseledets.Krieger.comap_twoSidedSat_le`: (literal) shift-invariance of the two-sided saturation.
* `Oseledets.Krieger.comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_twoSidedSat_le`: mod-0 shift-invariance.
* `Oseledets.Krieger.twoSidedSat_mono_of_codes`: mod-0 recovery monotonicity.
* `Oseledets.Krieger.IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0.of_codes`: recovery lifts a mod-0 two-sided generator.
* `Oseledets.Krieger.isGeneratingTwoSidedMod0_of_literal`: faithfulness ‚ÄĒ the (non-standard) literal
  condition is *stronger* than the (standard) mod-0 one.

## References

* Wolfgang Krieger, *On entropy and generators of measure-preserving transformations*,
  Trans. Amer. Math. Soc. **149** (1970), 453‚Äď464.
* Manfred Einsiedler, Elon Lindenstrauss and Thomas Ward, *Entropy in Ergodic Theory and
  Homogeneous Dynamics* (book in progress), Ch. 2 (generators, mod 0) and ¬ß3 (the Krieger generator
  theorem).
* Eli Glasner, *Ergodic Theory via Joinings*, Math. Surveys Monogr. **101**, AMS (2003) ‚ÄĒ Krieger
  chapter (generators are mod 0).
* Tomasz Downarowicz, *Entropy in Dynamical Systems*, Cambridge (2011), ¬ß4.2 (the strong-generator
  condition holds mod őľ).
-/

open MeasureTheory Function MeasurableSpace Filter

namespace Oseledets.Krieger

variable {őĪ : Type*} {őĻ őļ : Type*} [mőĪ : MeasurableSpace őĪ] [Fintype őĻ] [Fintype őļ]
  {őľ : Measure őĪ}

open Oseledets.Entropy

/-- The **two-sided itinerary ŌÉ-algebra** of a finite partition `P` under the automorphism `e`:
the supremum, over all integer iterates `e‚ĀŅ` (`n : ‚Ą§`), of the pulled-back generating ŌÉ-algebra
`ŌÉ(P)`. A set is `twoSidedSat e P`-measurable exactly when it is determined by the (two-sided)
`P`-itinerary `n ‚Ü¶ (the cell of P containing e‚ĀŅ x)`. By the design note above, the correct
two-sided generation condition asks for `twoSidedSat e P` to be the ambient ŌÉ-algebra **mod 0**
(`IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0`), not literally. Marked `@[reducible]` (its value is a
`MeasurableSpace`, a class type) so it unfolds for instance resolution and definitional rewriting,
mirroring `Oseledets.Entropy.generatedSigmaAlgebra`. -/
@[reducible]
noncomputable def twoSidedSat (e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ) (P : MeasurePartition őľ őĻ) : MeasurableSpace őĪ :=
  ‚®Ü n : ‚Ą§, MeasurableSpace.comap (ziter e n) (generatedSigmaAlgebra őľ P)

@[simp]
lemma twoSidedSat_def (e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ) (P : MeasurePartition őľ őĻ) :
    twoSidedSat e P = ‚®Ü n : ‚Ą§, MeasurableSpace.comap (ziter e n) (generatedSigmaAlgebra őľ P) :=
  rfl

/-- **Shift-invariance of the two-sided saturation.** Pulling the two-sided itinerary ŌÉ-algebra
`twoSidedSat e P` back by any iterate `eŠĶź` lands inside it again:
`comap (eŠĶź) (twoSidedSat e P) ‚Č§ twoSidedSat e P`.

A generator of `comap (eŠĶź) (twoSidedSat e P)` is `eŠĶź‚ĀĽ¬Ļ` of a generator of one of the `‚Ą§`-terms,
namely `comap (eŠĶź) (comap (e‚ĀŅ) ŌÉ(P)) = comap (e‚ĀŅ ‚ąė eŠĶź) ŌÉ(P) = comap (e^{n+m}) ŌÉ(P)` (using
`ziter_add`), which is the `(n + m)`-th term of the same `‚Ą§`-supremum. This is *exactly* where the
two-sided (`‚Ą§`) indexing is essential: the reindexing `n ‚Ü¶ n + m` is a bijection of `‚Ą§`, so no
terms are lost ‚ÄĒ a forward (`‚Ąē`) supremum would lose terms under a backward shift. -/
theorem comap_twoSidedSat_le (e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ) (P : MeasurePartition őľ őĻ) (m : ‚Ą§) :
    MeasurableSpace.comap (ziter e m) (twoSidedSat e P) ‚Č§ twoSidedSat e P := by
  rw [twoSidedSat_def, MeasurableSpace.comap_iSup]
  refine iSup_le fun n => ?_
  rw [MeasurableSpace.comap_comp, ‚Üź ziter_add]
  exact le_iSup (fun k : ‚Ą§ => MeasurableSpace.comap (ziter e k) (generatedSigmaAlgebra őľ P)) (n + m)

/-! ### The őľ-completion of a sub-ŌÉ-algebra, and its functoriality

We use `MeasureTheory.eventuallyMeasurableSpace m‚āÄ (ae őľ)` ‚ÄĒ the ŌÉ-algebra of sets `=ŠĶź[őľ]`-equal to
an `m‚āÄ`-measurable set ‚ÄĒ as the **őľ-completion** of the sub-ŌÉ-algebra `m‚āÄ`. The three lemmas below
(monotonicity, idempotence, and `comap`-commutation for a measure-preserving map) are all that the
mod-0 recovery needs; each keeps everything at the level of `MeasurableSpace`-`‚Č§`. -/

/-- **Monotonicity of the őľ-completion.** If `m‚āÄ ‚Č§ m‚āĀ` then their őľ-completions are ordered the same
way: an `m‚āÄ`-measurable approximant of `s` is in particular an `m‚āĀ`-measurable approximant. -/
theorem eventuallyMeasurableSpace_mono {m‚āÄ m‚āĀ : MeasurableSpace őĪ} (h : m‚āÄ ‚Č§ m‚āĀ) :
    eventuallyMeasurableSpace m‚āÄ (ae őľ) ‚Č§ eventuallyMeasurableSpace m‚āĀ (ae őľ) := by
  rintro s ‚ü®t, ht, hst‚ü©
  exact ‚ü®t, h t ht, hst‚ü©

/-- **Idempotence of the őľ-completion** (the "closure" half). The completion of the completion of
`m‚āÄ` is contained in the completion of `m‚āÄ`: if `s =ŠĶź t` and `t =ŠĶź u` with `u` `m‚āÄ`-measurable, then
`s =ŠĶź u`. -/
theorem eventuallyMeasurableSpace_idem {m‚āÄ : MeasurableSpace őĪ} :
    eventuallyMeasurableSpace (eventuallyMeasurableSpace m‚āÄ (ae őľ)) (ae őľ) ‚Č§
      eventuallyMeasurableSpace m‚āÄ (ae őľ) := by
  rintro s ‚ü®t, ‚ü®u, hu, htu‚ü©, hst‚ü©
  exact ‚ü®u, hu, hst.trans htu‚ü©

/-- **Preimage commutes with the őľ-completion** for a quasi-measure-preserving map `f` (in
particular a measure-preserving one). If `s =ŠĶź[őľ] t` then `f‚ĀĽ¬Ļs =ŠĶź[őľ] f‚ĀĽ¬Ļt`
(`QuasiMeasurePreserving.preimage_ae_eq`), so an `m‚āÄ`-completion set pulled back by `f` is an
`comap f m‚āÄ`-completion set:
`comap f (completion m‚āÄ) ‚Č§ completion (comap f m‚āÄ)`. -/
theorem comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_le {f : őĪ ‚Üí őĪ} {m‚āÄ : MeasurableSpace őĪ}
    (hf : Measure.QuasiMeasurePreserving f őľ őľ) :
    MeasurableSpace.comap f (eventuallyMeasurableSpace m‚āÄ (ae őľ)) ‚Č§
      eventuallyMeasurableSpace (MeasurableSpace.comap f m‚āÄ) (ae őľ) := by
  rintro _ ‚ü®s, ‚ü®t, ht, hst‚ü©, rfl‚ü©
  exact ‚ü®f ‚ĀĽ¬Ļ' t, ‚ü®t, ht, rfl‚ü©, hf.preimage_ae_eq hst‚ü©

/-! ### Mod-0 two-sided generation and coding -/

/-- `P` **two-sidedly generates `(őĪ, e, őľ)` mod 0** when the ambient ŌÉ-algebra `mőĪ` is contained in
the **őľ-completion** of the two-sided `P`-saturation:
`mőĪ ‚Č§ eventuallyMeasurableSpace (twoSidedSat e P) (ae őľ)`.

Equivalently (since `twoSidedSat e P ‚Č§ mőĪ` always), the őľ-completions of
`twoSidedSat e P` and of `mőĪ` agree: *every measurable set is recovered, up to a őľ-null set, by the
two-sided `P`-itinerary*. This is the standard "generator mod 0" condition of ergodic theory (see
the file header) and the faithful hypothesis/conclusion of Krieger's theorem ‚ÄĒ the literal equality
`twoSidedSat e P = mőĪ` (`IsGeneratingTwoSided`) is strictly stronger and is not what the classical
construction produces. -/
def IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0 (e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ) (P : MeasurePartition őľ őĻ) : Prop :=
  mőĪ ‚Č§ eventuallyMeasurableSpace (twoSidedSat e P) (ae őľ)

/-- **Mod-0 shift-invariance of the two-sided saturation.** For a measure-preserving `e`, pulling
the őľ-completion of `twoSidedSat e P` back by any iterate `eŠĶź` lands inside it again. Preimage
commutes with the completion (`comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_le`, since `eŠĶź` is
quasi-measure-preserving), and `comap (eŠĶź) (twoSidedSat e P) ‚Č§ twoSidedSat e P` literally
(`comap_twoSidedSat_le`), so completion-monotonicity (`eventuallyMeasurableSpace_mono`) finishes. -/
theorem comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_twoSidedSat_le (e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ)
    (he : MeasurePreserving (e : őĪ ‚Üí őĪ) őľ őľ) (P : MeasurePartition őľ őĻ) (m : ‚Ą§) :
    MeasurableSpace.comap (ziter e m)
        (eventuallyMeasurableSpace (twoSidedSat e P) (ae őľ)) ‚Č§
      eventuallyMeasurableSpace (twoSidedSat e P) (ae őľ) :=
  le_trans (comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_le
      (measurePreserving_ziter e he m).quasiMeasurePreserving)
    (eventuallyMeasurableSpace_mono (comap_twoSidedSat_le e P m))

/-- **Mod-0 recovery / refinement monotonicity.** If every cell of `Q` is recovered mod 0 by the
two-sided `P`-saturation (`ŌÉ(Q) ‚Č§ completion (twoSidedSat e P)`), then the *entire* two-sided
saturation of `Q` is contained in that completion: `twoSidedSat e Q ‚Č§ completion (twoSidedSat e P)`.

Each `‚Ą§`-term `comap (eŠĶź) ŌÉ(Q)` of `twoSidedSat e Q` is bounded, by `comap`-monotonicity in the
hypothesis, by `comap (eŠĶź) (completion (twoSidedSat e P))`, which is bounded by
`completion (twoSidedSat e P)` by mod-0 shift-invariance
(`comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_twoSidedSat_le`). Taking the supremum over `m` gives the claim. -/
theorem twoSidedSat_mono_of_codes (e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ) (he : MeasurePreserving (e : őĪ ‚Üí őĪ) őľ őľ)
    (P : MeasurePartition őľ őĻ) (Q : MeasurePartition őľ őļ)
    (hrec : generatedSigmaAlgebra őľ Q ‚Č§ eventuallyMeasurableSpace (twoSidedSat e P) (ae őľ)) :
    twoSidedSat e Q ‚Č§ eventuallyMeasurableSpace (twoSidedSat e P) (ae őľ) := by
  rw [twoSidedSat_def (P := Q)]
  refine iSup_le fun m => ?_
  exact le_trans (MeasurableSpace.comap_mono hrec)
    (comap_eventuallyMeasurableSpace_twoSidedSat_le e he P m)

/-- **Recovery lifts a mod-0 two-sided generator.** If `Q` two-sidedly generates `(őĪ, e, őľ)` mod 0
and the two-sided `P`-itinerary recovers each cell of `Q` mod 0
(`ŌÉ(Q) ‚Č§ completion (twoSidedSat e P)`), then `P` two-sidedly generates mod 0 as well.

`mőĪ ‚Č§ completion (twoSidedSat e Q)` (by `Q`'s mod-0 generation) and
`completion (twoSidedSat e Q) ‚Č§ completion (completion (twoSidedSat e P)) ‚Č§ completion
(twoSidedSat e P)` by mod-0 recovery monotonicity (`twoSidedSat_mono_of_codes`),
completion-monotonicity (`eventuallyMeasurableSpace_mono`), and completion-idempotence
(`eventuallyMeasurableSpace_idem`). Chaining gives `mőĪ ‚Č§ completion (twoSidedSat e P)`. This is the
mod-0 two-sided analogue of `Oseledets.Entropy.IsGenerating.mono_refine`. -/
theorem IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0.of_codes {e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ}
    (he : MeasurePreserving (e : őĪ ‚Üí őĪ) őľ őľ) {P : MeasurePartition őľ őĻ} {Q : MeasurePartition őľ őļ}
    (hQ : IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0 e Q)
    (hrec : generatedSigmaAlgebra őľ Q ‚Č§ eventuallyMeasurableSpace (twoSidedSat e P) (ae őľ)) :
    IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0 e P :=
  le_trans hQ
    (le_trans (eventuallyMeasurableSpace_mono (twoSidedSat_mono_of_codes e he P Q hrec))
      eventuallyMeasurableSpace_idem)

/-! ### Faithfulness -/

/-- **Faithfulness: the literal condition is stronger than the mod-0 one.** If `P` two-sidedly
generates in the (non-standard) literal sense `twoSidedSat e P = mőĪ` (`IsGeneratingTwoSided`), then
it does so mod 0. Hence the mod-0 statement is a genuine *weakening* of the literal one, and the
headline phrased with `IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0` is faithful to Krieger's theorem (whose generators
are mod 0) while remaining provable by the classical a.e. construction.

`mőĪ = twoSidedSat e P` (literal generation) embeds into its own őľ-completion by
`le_eventuallyMeasurableSpace`; `le_of_eq ‚Ä¶ .symm` supplies the equality without rewriting under the
`őľ`-indexed completion (which would fail the motive check). The hypothesis `h` is, definitionally,
the equality `twoSidedSat e P = mőĪ` (`IsGeneratingTwoSided` is `@[reducible]`-unfolds to the same
`‚®Ü`-ŌÉ-algebra as `twoSidedSat`). -/
theorem isGeneratingTwoSidedMod0_of_literal {e : őĪ ‚ČÉŠĶź őĪ} {P : MeasurePartition őľ őĻ}
    (h : IsGeneratingTwoSided e P) : IsGeneratingTwoSidedMod0 e P :=
  le_trans (le_of_eq h.symm) le_eventuallyMeasurableSpace

end Oseledets.Krieger
